{"type":"step-attempt","step":"spec-review","sessionId":"a8195c37-b243-42ea-85b8-d80b5af39348","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/design-topic-emission/spec-review-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"medium","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/design-topic-emission/spec.md","title":"Body content may contain bare `---` that confuses frontmatter parsers","rationale":"LLM-generated `title` and `rationale` could include a line consisting solely of `---`, which some YAML/frontmatter parsers treat as a closing delimiter. This could cause the `id`/`source` frontmatter fields to be silently dropped. The spec does not require the implementer to escape or sanitize bare `---` in the body."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/design-topic-emission/spec.md","title":"stdout summary line format is not specified","rationale":"The requirement states 'a single stdout line reporting the count and the destination directory' but gives no example format string. Tests that assert on the exact output may diverge across implementations. This is non-blocking but the format should be pinned in tasks.md T-03 to prevent ambiguity."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/design-topic-emission/tasks.md","title":"T-02 does not show how to retrieve DecisionRecord.selectedOption after isFindingDecided check","rationale":"`isFindingDecided` returns a boolean, but `renderTopicFile` needs the full `DecisionRecord` (specifically `selectedOption.label` and `selectedOption.consequence`). T-02 says to use `isFindingDecided` without showing the follow-up `state.decisions.find(d => d.step === step && d.findingKey === key)` pattern. The mechanism is derivable from existing code but the gap could cause an implementer to stop at the bool check."}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/design-topic-emission/design.md","title":"D9 correctly enumerates all 3 ResolvedDesignLayer construction sites","rationale":"orchestrator.ts noopDesignLayer, archive.ts disabledDesignLayer, and resolveDesignLayerConfig are all identified. TypeScript's required-field check on the interface will catch any missed sites at typecheck time, so the risk of silent regression is negligible."},{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/design-topic-emission/design.md","title":"D7 placement before mark-hook is the correct structural guarantee for independence","rationale":"Placing emitDesignTopics before the mark-hook block ensures that even if mark-hook returns error early, topic emission has already run and staged its files. This structurally satisfies the independence requirement without needing conditional logic."}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-07-09T13:57:12.650Z","endedAt":"2026-07-09T14:01:55.108Z"}
